# FouriqTech SEO Audit & Competitor Analysis

## 1. Technical SEO Audit (Local Codebase)
Since FouriqTech is currently in development (Vite/React single-page application) and not yet a live indexed site, this audit focuses on the structural code readiness for SEO based on the [fouriqtech-seo-config.yaml](file:///Users/karmjoshi/Desktop/FourIqTech/fouriqtech-seo-config.yaml).

### 🚨 Critical Issues Identified
1. **Missing Meta Tags ([index.html](file:///Users/karmjoshi/Desktop/FourIqTech/index.html))**: The site currently only has a basic `<title>FouriqTech — Next-Gen Digital Services</title>`. It is missing the targeted meta description defined in your config.
2. **Missing Dynamic SEO Manager**: As a React Single Page Application (SPA), search engine crawlers struggle to index dynamic routes without Server-Side Rendering (SSR) or a dynamic head manager. Tools like `react-helmet-async` are not installed.
3. **No Schema Markup**: LocalBusiness, Service, and Organization schema markup are entirely absent from the codebase.
4. **Missing XML Sitemap & Robots.txt**: These crucial crawler directives do not exist in the `public/` directory.
5. **Missing Canonical Tags**: Required to prevent duplicate content issues as the site scales.

### ✅ Quick Wins 
1. **Implement `react-helmet-async`**: Allows dynamic updating of `title` and `meta` descriptions per route (e.g., `/web-design-services`).
2. **Inject static JSON-LD Schema**: Add the `LocalBusiness` schema directly into [index.html](file:///Users/karmjoshi/Desktop/FourIqTech/index.html) as a fallback.
3. **Add `robots.txt`**: Create a basic `robots.txt` in the `public` folder allowing all crawlers.

